<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-11-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Breckinridge</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-11-02"><hi rend="italic">November 2,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President has sent to Livadia, in response to a telegram from Emperor
                            Nicolas, a message of sincere regret and condolence. You will make this
                            known to M. de Giers, expressing the sincere sympathy of the President
                            and people of the United States with the Russian people in their deep
                            grief.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>